---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Catalyst Neuromorphic" description="Spiking neural network processors. Event-driven, on-chip learning, sub-watt power." hasFog={true}>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="pt-36 pb-16 px-6 md:px-12" style="position:relative;z-index:1;">
    <div style="max-width:700px;margin:0 auto;text-align:center;">
      <p class="text-sm text-catalyst-blue font-medium tracking-wider uppercase mb-5">About</p>
      <h1 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif; font-size:clamp(2.6rem,5.5vw,4.2rem); font-weight:700; letter-spacing:-0.04em; line-height:1;">
        Neuromorphic processors for edge inference.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-base text-white/35 mt-5" style="line-height:1.7;">Event-driven spiking neural network hardware. Designed, validated on FPGA, targeting ASIC.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT WE BUILD -->
  <section class="pb-24 px-6 md:px-12" style="position:relative;z-index:1;">
    <div style="max-width:640px;margin:0 auto;">
      <div class="card-glass reveal" style="padding:clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem);">
        <div style="position:relative;z-index:2;">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">What we build</h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-sm text-white/40" style="line-height:1.75;">
            <p>Catalyst designs spiking neural network processors. The architecture is event-driven &mdash; neurons only fire and consume energy when there's a spike to process. Cores support on-chip learning (STDP, reward-modulated three-factor, programmable microcode rules), so models adapt at inference time without retraining.</p>
            <p>The current generation (N2) implements full Loihi 2 feature parity: 128 neuromorphic cores, 5 neuron models, 4 synapse formats, variable-precision weights (1&ndash;16 bit), graded spike payloads, and a programmable microcode engine that replaces the fixed datapath. All designed from a blank Verilog file, not derived from existing IP.</p>
            <p>Everything runs on real FPGA hardware today. The cloud API lets you submit spiking networks and get spike train results without owning a board.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DIVIDER -->
  <div style="width:100%;max-width:400px;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,rgba(59,130,246,0.2),transparent);margin:0 auto;"></div>

  <!-- FPGA RESULTS -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 md:px-12" style="position:relative;z-index:1;">
    <div style="max-width:640px;margin:0 auto;">
      <h2 class="reveal text-[clamp(1.8rem,3vw,2.4rem)] font-bold tracking-tight mb-6" style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;">Hardware validation.</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-sm text-white/40 reveal" style="line-height:1.75;">
        <p>Designs are validated on AWS F2 FPGA instances (Xilinx UltraScale+) and Xilinx Kria K26 SoMs. These aren't simulations &mdash; the RTL runs on physical fabric at clock speed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-6">
        {[
          { title: 'N4 &mdash; AWS F2 (UltraScale+)', desc: '4-core, 62.5 MHz. Validated: neuron membrane dynamics, synaptic weight formats (1&ndash;16 bit), cross-core mesh routing, axonal delays, STDP learning, graded spike payloads, multi-compartment dendrites, microcode execution, and state isolation. 14,983 timesteps/sec sustained throughput.' },
          { title: 'N4-Edge &mdash; Kria K26 SoM', desc: '8-core variant targeting embedded deployment. 3,036 LUTs (2.59% of fabric), 0.378 W total board power, WNS +3.301 ns. Same test coverage as F2 build. Targets $5&ndash;$20 FPGA modules for sub-watt edge inference.' },
          { title: 'N3 &mdash; AWS F2 (UltraScale+)', desc: '8-core tile at 83.3 MHz. All 68 architectural features enabled: hardware virtualisation, per-tile learning engines, silicon metaplasticity, adaptive neuron models. 14,500 timesteps/sec. WNS 0.000 ns (timing met exactly).' },
          { title: 'N2 &mdash; AWS F2 (UltraScale+)', desc: 'Full 128-core design. 228K LUTs, 1.913 W measured FPGA power. Validated against CPU reference simulator &mdash; bit-exact spike output match across all neuron models and synapse formats.' },
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="card-glass" style="padding:1.25rem 1.5rem;">
            <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-white/75 mb-1.5" style="position:relative;z-index:2;" set:html={item.title}></div>
            <div class="text-xs text-white/30" style="line-height:1.6;position:relative;z-index:2;" set:html={item.desc}></div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DIVIDER -->
  <div style="width:100%;max-width:400px;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,rgba(59,130,246,0.2),transparent);margin:0 auto;"></div>

  <!-- ASIC PROJECTIONS -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 md:px-12" style="position:relative;z-index:1;">
    <div style="max-width:640px;margin:0 auto;">
      <h2 class="reveal text-[clamp(1.8rem,3vw,2.4rem)] font-bold tracking-tight mb-6" style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;">ASIC projections.</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-sm text-white/40 reveal" style="line-height:1.75;">
        <p>Synthesis-based estimates from the N2 architecture using standard cell libraries. These are projections from gate-level synthesis, not tape-out results.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal card-glass mt-6" style="padding:clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2rem);">
        <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:auto 1fr 1fr;gap:0.6rem 2rem;position:relative;z-index:2;">
          <div class="text-sm text-white/30"></div>
          <div class="text-sm text-white/50 font-semibold">28 nm</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-white/50 font-semibold">130 nm</div>
          {[
            ['Die area', '~9.3 mm\u00B2', '~186 mm\u00B2'],
            ['Power', '19\u201338 mW', '96\u2013191 mW'],
            ['Target clock', '500 MHz', '125 MHz'],
            ['Neuron capacity', '131K per chip', '131K per chip'],
          ].map(([label, col1, col2]) => (
            <>
              <div class="text-sm text-white/30">{label}</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-white/50">{col1}</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-white/50">{col2}</div>
            </>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DIVIDER -->
  <div style="width:100%;max-width:400px;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,rgba(59,130,246,0.2),transparent);margin:0 auto;"></div>

  <!-- WHERE WE ARE -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 md:px-12" style="position:relative;z-index:1;">
    <div style="max-width:640px;margin:0 auto;">
      <h2 class="reveal text-[clamp(1.8rem,3vw,2.4rem)] font-bold tracking-tight mb-6" style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;">Current status.</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-sm text-white/40 reveal" style="line-height:1.75;">
        <p>Four processor generations designed (N1&ndash;N4). All validated on FPGA. Three papers published on Zenodo with open access. The cloud API is live and serving requests. The N4-Edge variant targets sub-watt embedded deployment on $5&ndash;$20 FPGA modules.</p>
        <p>Next step is manufactured silicon. The architecture is complete and the RTL is synthesis-ready. We're raising funding to tape out at 28 nm.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DIVIDER -->
  <div style="width:100%;max-width:400px;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,rgba(59,130,246,0.2),transparent);margin:0 auto;"></div>

  <!-- COMPANY -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 md:px-12" style="position:relative;z-index:1;">
    <div style="max-width:640px;margin:0 auto;">
      <h2 class="reveal text-[clamp(1.8rem,3vw,2.4rem)] font-bold tracking-tight mb-6" style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;">Company.</h2>
      <div class="reveal card-glass" style="padding:clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2rem);">
        <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:auto 1fr;gap:0.6rem 2rem;position:relative;z-index:2;">
          {[
            ['Founded', 'February 2026'],
            ['Entity', 'Catalyst Neuromorphic Ltd (UK)'],
            ['Founder', 'Henry Shulayev Barnes'],
            ['Affiliation', 'University of Aberdeen'],
            ['Programme', 'Techscaler (Scotland)'],
            ['RTL license', 'BSL 1.1 (proprietary)'],
            ['SDK license', 'BSL 1.1'],
            ['API client', 'MIT (open source)'],
            ['Papers', 'Open access (Zenodo)'],
          ].map(([label, value]) => (
            <>
              <div class="text-sm text-white/30">{label}</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-white/50">{value}</div>
            </>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- GET IN TOUCH -->
  <section class="connect-section" style="position:relative;z-index:1;">
    <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif; font-size:clamp(2.4rem,5vw,3.6rem); font-weight:700; letter-spacing:-0.035em; line-height:1.08; text-align:center; margin-bottom:18px;">Get in touch.</h2>
    <p class="connect-email"><a href="mailto:henry@catalyst-neuromorphic.com">henry@catalyst-neuromorphic.com</a></p>
    <div class="connect-grid">
      <a href="https://github.com/catalyst-neuromorphic" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="connect-card">
        <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M15 22v-4a4.8 4.8 0 0 0-1-3.5c3 0 6-2 6-5.5.08-1.25-.27-2.48-1-3.5.28-1.15.28-2.35 0-3.5 0 0-1 0-3 1.5-2.64-.5-5.36-.5-8 0C6 2 5 2 5 2c-.3 1.15-.3 2.35 0 3.5A5.4 5.4 0 0 0 4 9c0 3.5 3 5.5 6 5.5-.39.49-.68 1.05-.85 1.65S8.93 17.38 9 18v4"/><path d="M9 18c-4.51 2-5-2-7-2"/></svg>
        <span class="connect-label">GitHub</span>
        <span class="connect-sub">Source & contributions</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/research" class="connect-card">
        <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M2 3h6a4 4 0 0 1 4 4v14a3 3 0 0 0-3-3H2z"/><path d="M22 3h-6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v14a3 3 0 0 1 3-3h7z"/></svg>
        <span class="connect-label">Research</span>
        <span class="connect-sub">Papers & benchmarks</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style is:global>
    .connect-section {
      max-width: 1100px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 80px 32px 100px;
    }
    .connect-email {
      font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
      font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 16px;
      margin-bottom: 56px;
    }
    .connect-email a {
      color: rgba(59,130,246,0.8);
      text-decoration: none;
      transition: color 0.3s;
    }
    .connect-email a:hover { color: #60A5FA; }
    .connect-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: 20px;
    }
    .connect-card {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 36px 24px;
      border-radius: 20px;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: #fff;
      background: linear-gradient(165deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.12) 0%, rgba(255,255,255,0.05) 35%, rgba(255,255,255,0.025) 100%);
      backdrop-filter: blur(28px) saturate(190%) brightness(1.06);
      -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(28px) saturate(190%) brightness(1.06);
      border: 1px solid transparent;
      box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.45), inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.14), inset 0 -1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
      transition: box-shadow 0.5s, transform 0.3s;
    }
    .connect-card:hover {
      transform: translateY(-3px);
      box-shadow: 0 12px 48px rgba(0,0,0,0.55), inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.18), inset 0 -1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    }
    .connect-card::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      border-radius: 20px;
      padding: 1px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(59,130,246,0.22) 0%, rgba(59,130,246,0.06) 25%, rgba(59,130,246,0.02) 50%, rgba(59,130,246,0.06) 75%, rgba(59,130,246,0.18) 100%);
      -webkit-mask: linear-gradient(#fff 0 0) content-box, linear-gradient(#fff 0 0);
      -webkit-mask-composite: xor;
      mask-composite: exclude;
      pointer-events: none;
      z-index: 5;
      opacity: 0.55;
      transition: opacity 0.4s;
    }
    .connect-card:hover::before { opacity: 1; }
    .connect-card svg {
      color: #60A5FA;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      position: relative;
      z-index: 2;
    }
    .connect-label {
      font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
      position: relative;
      z-index: 2;
    }
    .connect-sub {
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4);
      position: relative;
      z-index: 2;
    }
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .connect-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
  </style>

</BaseLayout>
